To have the text "NEW DESIGNS" appear on the `ProjectsBtn` component when displayed on a mobile device, you can use Tailwind CSS's responsive utility classes. These classes allow you to conditionally apply styles based on the size of the viewport. In this case, you'd want to hide the arrow icon and show the "NEW DESIGNS" text on small screens.

As of my knowledge cutoff date in March 2023, the Tailwind CSS framework uses the prefix `sm:` for small screens (by default, screens 640px and wider), `md:` for medium screens, and so forth. For smaller screens (mobile devices) without any prefix, you would use the styles directly.

You can update your `ProjectsBtn` component by removing the `useState` and hover logic, instead relying solely on Tailwind CSS classes for responsiveness:

```jsx
import Image from "next/image";
import Link from "next/link";

import { HiArrowRight } from "react-icons/hi2";

const ProjectsBtn = () => {
  return (
    <div className="mx-auto pb-20 xl:mx-0 hover:animate-pulse transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out group">
      <Link
        href="/designs"
        className="relative w-[185px] h-[185px] flex justify-center items-center bg-circleStar bg-cover bg-center bg-no-repeat group"
      >
        <Image
          src="/black.gif"
          alt="rounded text"
          width={185}
          height={185}
          className="bg-cover w-full h-full max-w-[141px] max-h-[148px] pointer-events-none select-none"
        />
        <span
          className="absolute z-10 left-0 right-0 top-1/2 transform -translate-y-1/2 text-center hidden sm:block"
          style={{ color: '#f13024', fontWeight: 'bold', fontSize: '1rem'}}
        >
          NEW DESIGNS
        </span>
        <HiArrowRight
          className="absolute text-4xl sm:hidden transition-transform duration-300"
          style={{ color: '#f13024' }}
          aria-hidden
        />
      </Link>
    </div>
  );
};

export default ProjectsBtn;
```

In the updated component, the `HiArrowRight` icon is now hidden on small screens (using the `sm:hidden` class which applies to screens 640px and wider, so the icon is hidden on smaller screens) and the "NEW DESIGNS" text is displayed instead. Vice versa, the text will be hidden (using the `hidden sm:block` class) and the icon will be shown on larger screens.

**Note:** The breakpoint for styling might change depending on your Tailwind CSS configuration. If `640px` is not the breakpoint you want for hiding the icon and showing the text, you can adjust the prefix to the appropriate breakpoint for your use case (`md:`, `lg:`, etc.).

Tailwind should be set up properly in your project for these utility classes to take effect. Ensure your project's Tailwind configuration does not alter the default breakpoints if you intend to use them as suggested.

